    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite seven credibility factors achieving levels below required levels and six factors not assessed, the ensemble 95th-percentile NIH prediction remained below the absolute clinical threshold across all five operating points. The Monte Carlo UQ results provide sufficient confidence that the model conservatively bounds hemolysis risk for the intended COU. The assessment team accepted the submission with the understanding that identified epistemic gaps will be addressed in a follow-on validation study prior to pre-market submission. The primary hemolysis validation result (in-vitro NIH comparison) provides the strongest quantitative evidence supporting this decision.",
